.TH "mce_threshold_create_device" 9 "mce_threshold_create_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mce_threshold_create_device \- Create the per-CPU MCE threshold device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mce_threshold_create_device
.BI "(unsigned int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
The plugged in CPU
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create directories and files for all valid threshold banks.

This is invoked from the CPU hotplug callback which was installed in
\fBmcheck_init_device\fP. The invocation happens in context of the hotplug
thread running on \fIcpu\fP.  The callback is invoked on all CPUs which are
online when the callback is installed or during a real hotplug event.
